Package fr.cnrs.iees.graph

Interface Element

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Identity, Specialized, fr.ens.biologie.generic.Textable
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    Edge, Node, TreeNode
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ALDataEdge, ALDataNode, ALEdge, ALNode, ALReadOnlyDataEdge, ALReadOnlyDataNode, ElementAdapter, SimpleDataTreeNode, SimpleReadOnlyDataTreeNode, SimpleTreeNode, TreeGraphDataNode, TreeGraphNode, TreeGraphReadOnlyDataNode
    public interface Element
extends Specialized, fr.ens.biologie.generic.Textable, Identity

    A basic interface for graph elements. Graph elements are connected (cf. the Connected interface), but they also have other features captured in this interface:

    • They must have a unique identifier for internal graph management (Identity interface)
    • They should display information about their state in a human-readable way (Textable interface)
    • They may belong to groups of elements with a similar behaviour, indicated by a label or classId (Specialized interface)
    Author:
    Jacques Gignoux - 9 mai 2019
